flavor_text: Tenacity prevails when hopes die.
"In your misguided attempt to subvert the law, you have eloquently explained why the law must exist."
"We don't choose who comes here. We choose how long they stay."
Seen through Rakdos eyes, a cruel betrayal is a hilarious stunt.
The shield took a year to craft, a month to enchant, and a decade to master—all for one glorious moment.
The passionate intensity of the Ghitu tempered by the cool insight of Tolarian training.
"You and your ship will make a fine addition to my fleet."
"Damn the cannons, mates. Charge!"
Every odyssey begins with a single step.
Inner strength is never seen until it makes all the difference.
The best of their trade know every bolt of their rigs, stem to stern.

"The absence of binocular vision imposes certain challenges for a flying creature, which are overcome via echolocation."
—Simic research notes
An ancient device recovered from a thawing glacier high in the Karplusan mountains.
Most smiths shape metal, but some prefer more delicate materials.
If you can't find a doorway, make one.
The problem isn't the indrik's enthusiasm, it's Ravnica's lack of guardrails.

"Approach from behind. That way, if it does charge, at least you aren't in front of it."
—Vivien Reid
"Our lives, our homes, and all our history are at risk. Do not speak to me of peace."
As the ship approached, the jade totem rose high overhead. Power rippled. Eyes of stone glowed and crackled. Out hissed a breath of the world, and a windstorm came alive.

"When one of us prospers, the pride prospers."
—Jazal Goldmane
"You cannot defend others if your own well-being is neglected."

"A rare and fascinating phenomenon."
—Tamiyo
Neither its appearance nor its temperature varies as the years pass, an eternal testament to the forces that shaped Dominaria.
Whether it is magical, lucky, or merely old, it is cherished, and that gives it power.
Multani's mind grasped for consciousness as rage itself rebuilt his body.
It is taller than all but the tallest trees, and older than all but the oldest.

"If we cannot have peace, we will have justice."
—Aurelia
She sings for all those who have been silenced.
Orcs have been enemies of the Legion of Dusk since it was formed, and the entire race has been declared anathema.
Captain Angrath cares less about treasure than mayhem. If he can't leave Ixalan, he'll burn the plane down.
Inspiration is red as rubies, flowing like honeyed wine.
Divining the future is easy when you hold the power to sway it.
"As I desire, so it shall be." —Nicol Bolas

"Llanowar's boughs are ever ready To unleash an autumn of steel leaves."
—"Song of Freyalise"
Knowledge itself is neither good nor evil. Just as the wrong book in the wrong hands could doom all existence, the same book in the right hands could save it.
The Tolarian Academies are known for their magical research, powerful sorcerers, and accidental destruction of ecosystems.
A ray of hope breaks through the shroud of rain.
Some storms never blow over.

flavor_text:
"I'm not picky about what comes up, but the less decay, the better."
—Liliana Vess
Law is the voice of reason.
Law is the light of civilization.
"It is impious to admit, but I do enjoy pirate blood. Something in the salty tang of it, the spice of rebellion."
Dimir assassinations are choreographed like dance routines. Each challenge is anticipated and countered with graceful ease.
"I won't abandon the Weatherlight. My destiny is to serve at Jhoira's side. This 'illness' means I must trust my faith more and myself less."
"Let no trace of the vampires' foulness remain."
A power vacuum for the Azorius. A keepsake for Vraska.

flavor_text: When the Erstwhile were unearthed from their tombs, they became a ready-made army for Vraska.
His arrows are fletched with feathers from the greatest of the winged dinosaurs.
Streams of gold and bright feathers flash in the orb, visions of past and future.
"My flock flew from a distant continent ruined by cataclysm and war. Benalia gave us shelter to end our exodus."
"My skill sharpens with each beat of my wings."
"They say that perfection is unattainable, but they say that about flight too."
"The fools have done it." —Tishana
In preparation for the conflict all foresaw, the Golgari called upon an army that had slept for millennia beneath the city.

"Imagine a gigantic pine cone that's extremely territorial and always in a foul mood."
—Zhosmir, urban huntmaster
The Church of Dusk teaches there is no gain without loss, no triumph without sacrifice, no drink of exquisite crimson without a dying gasp.

"If the populace fears our authority, then I'd say we have an appropriately sensible populace."
—Dovin Baan
Thanks to the magic of his Writ of Passage, alms beasts lumbered aside, anarchs bowed their heads, and even Rakdos acrobats rolled their spikewheels out of his way.

"Mandatory lockets enable the tracking of all Senate personnel for improved security and efficiency."
—Dovin Baan
"These new thopters are all well and good, but four eyes are better than none."

flavor_text: "The walls of Argive were built by a peaceful dynastic union that has guarded us against war for fifteen centuries. The lesson is clear."
A baloth only cares about the many things it eats and the few things that eat it.
For Sarkhan Vol, the dragon is the purest expression of life's savage splendor.
"Your spirits can rest in peace, for your debts are paid."
"Don't stop till your horns come out their back."
The Dimir rarely make statements, but when they do, the message is clear.

"Bats are welcome to eat thousands of my pets. I have multitudes more that will ultimately eat the bats."
—Izoni
You can hear their tolling only when your debt is due.
The Izzet love replicating results.
"The tiniest mouse speaks louder to me than all the festival crowds on Tin Street."

Bedazzle deals 2 damage to target opponent or planeswalker.', 'watermark': 'rakdos', 'artist': 'Randy Vargas'}]

flavor_text:
"It's easy to get taken in by the spectacle, to enjoy a bit of naughty amusement. But make no mistake: the Cult of Rakdos is a danger."
—Tajic
"The trick to talking sense into Keldons is getting them to hold still."
Predators try to separate the young, old, or injured from the rest of the herd. The alternative is crushing defeat.
Its roaring challenge is punctuated by the slam of its tail on the earth, rousing the herds of the plains.

"The true measure of all heroes is not what they achieve, but who they inspire."
—Triumph of Gerrard
"Some aspire to climb the mountain of Honor. The Benalish are born upon its peak, and from there ascend among the stars." —History of Benalia
"I am my life's work."

"To survive exceptional times we must adapt by exceptional means."
—Vannifar
"In the death of the foe lies the resurrection of the faithful."
"They shall give us all they have as penance for their resistance. Their ships. Their goods. Their rebellious blood."
Vampires, the noble class of old Torrezon, are guided by their dual loyalties to church and crown.
It spilled the blood of one elder dragon. In Gideon's hands, it may yet taste another's.

"The pain of searing iron and razor edges pales beside the pleasure of performance."
—Judith
"Watch carefully. The gap between death and victory is thinner than your blade."
"No shadow remains for you to hide in." —Caparocti Sunborn
Enchanted by mage-smiths and blessed by priests, Benalish windows let in light and cast out darkness.
"My heart is not mine, it is Belzenlok's. All hearts are his, and all blood." —"Rite of Belzenlok"
It withers fruit and flesh alike.
"I see you, shiny soldiers, but you won't see me."
When a paladin undertaking the Blood Fast finally gives in to hunger, the violence is sudden, explosive, and complete.
Life is a show, and death its final performance.
Predicting the future is a messy business.
Blood seeks blood, and nothing shall hold back its hunger.
The stone whispers tales of darkness and fire. She replies, "Tell me more."
As the struggle raged for control of the Immortal Sun, the world grew dark under a blood-red sky.
"Bring me an angel feather, and I will give you one death in return. There can be no turning back once the candle is lit." —Whisper, blood liturgist
The only force on Ixalan not interested in finding the golden city is Ixalan itself.
A new gathering for a new age.
He has the biggest bashing stick, so it's a safe bet he's the leader.

"They are gentle herbivores, despite their size. Approach cautiously, and hum a tune to let them know you mean no harm."
—Vivien Reid
Jaharg discovered that the shapes and symmetries so pleasing to the sculptor's eye also yielded a well-balanced bludgeon.
"Want to sink a ship? Blow a hole in the hull. Want to kill a regisaur? Same answer." —Captain Brandis Thorn
"You don't tame a horncrest. You convince it that it's easier to destroy something else." —Amautl, knight of Atzocan
Its roar is the clatter of a thousand bones.

"I can think of worse ways to go. On second thought, maybe not."
—Ludevic, necro-alchemist
"Not my first edition of *The Advokist and the Urchin*!"
"Send your champion. I could use a light workout."

"The more trust breaks down, the more we must throw open the front gates."
—Aurelia

"We pass these along to our fellow soldiers to recognize deeds of valor. It won't stay with you for long."
—Alovnek, Boros guildmage
"Lately I've seen the biggest bounties of my career—and for the biggest names."

"I am the very soul of battle, but even I would never advise open war with the Conclave."
—Aurelia
"Why squabble for trinkets when we could be living large off all this gold?" —Admiral Beckett Brass
Finders, keepers.

"One beginning, many paths."
—Vannifar
Vampires know blood and the systems that carry it. And they know exactly where to strike to set it free.
"In you go, big guy. Watch your head."

"Nicol Bolas destroyed my world. I owe it to Skalla to celebrate all life, no matter how dangerous."
—Vivien Reid
"I can't bear to see another plane broken before I make my own home whole. I'm sorry, but my watch is over."
Never underestimate the power of panache.

"Even rats hoard their treasures. Are your precious thing so different?"
—Izoni

"From a great bonfire at the dawn of time, the first Gruul kindled their rage. The same flame burns in you."
—Kroshkar, Gruul shaman
"Tilonalli's searing rays carry the spark of life's eventual destruction as all light fades." —Chitlati, Lightning Rider
The ostentatious splendor of the Orzhov church was just asking to be smashed.
"All hail the Demonlord Belzenlok, Evincar of the Stronghold, Scion of Darkness, Doom of Fools, Lord of the Wastes, Master of the Ebon Hand, Eternal Patriarch of the Cabal . . ."
"The Demonlord has ruled every age. Every ruin, myth, and nightmare proves his power." — "Rite of Belzenlok"
The seat of Belzenlok's power, the Stronghold serves as the gathering place for the Cabal as their dark influence spreads from Urborg.
When a cacophodon is angry, the whole jungle knows.
"Take their faces. The lips of these unbelievers may yet honor the Demonlord."
Benalish citizens born under the same constellations share a star-clan. Their loyalty to one another interlaces the Seven Houses.
By the law of church and crown, vampires feed only on the blood of the guilty—those declared heretics, rebels, or enemies of war.

"Within the song of Mat'Selesnya, one becomes all."
—Heruj, Selesnya hierophant

The first goblin tried to swim the canal. The second built a raft. The last and craftiest goblin launched herself from a firecannon and soared over the canal, trailing smoke. All were eaten, but only one was cooked.
"I decide what stands in my way."
Selesnya guildmages do not sleep so the rest of the conclave can.
"We sail. We plunder. Then we dance."
Sun Empire commanders are well versed in advanced martial strategy. Still, the correct maneuver is usually to deploy the giant, implacable death lizard.

flavor_text: No scrap of nutrition goes to waste in the undercity.
"Your life is finished, your name lost, and your work forgotten. It is as though Mazeura never existed." — Chainer's Torment

"I am sewer-king!" said Rat. "I am quick and cunning and I know every tunnel."
"No, I am king!" said Zombie. "I am cold and deadly and no rot can harm me."
Then Croc came and ate them both.
As the hyperstormic generator crept past redline, a being emerged from the arc.
Let the Dimir worry about witnesses. For the Rakdos, screams count as applause.

"The centaurs are truly free. Never will they be tamed by temptation or controlled by fear. They live in total harmony, a feat not yet achieved by our kind."
—Ramal, sage of Westgate
"Please accept this offering. I sincerely hope to leave my mace at my side."
"Drench these golden streets in the blood of our enemies."
Grand Warlord Radha's challengers are always defeated, but she rewards the most passionate with the Flame of Keld. After that, they burn for her.
"It is not your time. The Legion still needs your blade."
"Honor rides before us. All we have to do is catch up." —Danitha Capashen
"I knew I should have stayed with the boat. Always stay with the boat!"
It doesn't hold grudges. It runs them down and impales them.
While other pirates prowl for treasure, Captain Parrish plunders secrets.
"My specialty is theoretical universal limits and ways to circumvent them."
Despite its appearance, it's anything but defenseless.
No guilds—that is her rule. The House vampires unnerve her. The Combine would dissect her, the Legion burn her, the Conclave "cure" her. The shadows are all the family she needs.
If you can see your breath, it's too late to run.
By guild tradition, any puddle of multicolored light on the cobblestones can serve as neutral ground.

"I do as I choose with what is mine. And it is all mine."
—Nicol Bolas

"The shortest path between two points is not always the safest."
—Tamina, district guide
All those who trade in questions must answer to the Dimir.

"Oh, you fellas are going to love the lockup. Excellent gruel. Very low ceilings."
—Libuse, Boros sergeant
"These are your streets. Defend them! This is your neighborhood. Honor it! This is your city. Save it!"

"Little goblin. Big noise."
—Ruric Thar
In their final moments, the demons gazed upon grace in its purest form.
"The sun creates, sustains, and consumes so it can create again." —Caparocti Sunborn

"The best way to keep a secret is to forget it."
—Lazav
"Make way! It's time for the final act!"
The sunlight falls pristine on the temple at Epityr, softened by the remembered shadows of angelic saviors' wings.
Flotsam held together by optimism.
For generations, the inhabitants of Orvada have hungered for turtle soup. For generations, the turtles have frustrated their ambitions.

"Reports of Gruul rioters in four districts. Start with the big ones and work your way up."
—Libuse, Boros sergeant

flavor_text: If you feel the ground quake, run. If you hear its bellow, flee. If you see its teeth, it's too late.

"Might doesn't just build empires. It protects them."
—Inti, Sun Empire knight
In the wake of Niv-Mizzet's disappearance, Ral found himself leading the guild. He had dreamed of this day, but couldn't help feeling like a pawn in someone else's game.
"Just as leaves fall and the tree blooms again, one day I will fall and the Conclave will endure."

"What makes a frog lizard any worse than a bird horse? Prejudice against the Simic, that's what! It's unfair!"
—Thados Arquef,
Guardian Project biomancer

flavor_text: First your whole life flashes before your eyes. Then you have considerable time to reflect on every regret as you plummet.
For a price, the floating city of High and Dry offers all the amenities a pirate could want: rest, recreation, and revenge.

Few Ravnicans are aware of the vast reefs in their world's hidden ocean. Far beneath the great sinkholes, where the light is blue and dim, merfolk tend the coral labyrinths that feed the benthic ecosystem.
Nothing tastes finer to an ooze than a priceless family heirloom.
"This sort of innovation occurs when you set out to improve an electric tea kettle and misplace a decimal."
No lock of iron is a match for Vraska's will of stone.

"The healers of Bant are second to none. I owe then a great deal for their tutelage."
—Ajani Goldmane
Possession is eleven-tenths of the pirate code.
The Legion's conquistadors could endure Ixalan's sun. Their forts could withstand a charging ceratops. But nothing can stop a ceratops strengthened by the sun.
"Our survival, like theirs, depends on our ability to work together." —Huatli, to Tishana
Amidst the darkest ashes grow the strongest seeds.
The Izzet mage knew she would neither get her thermoinverter back nor have the satisfaction of exploding it herself.

"The Dimir may look all they want. We never grow tired of swatting their bugs."
—Heruj, Selesnya hierophant
If your ears bleed, it's a party. If your eyes bleed, it's a Rakdos party.
Its ventricles weep venom, and it consumes only poison.
"Keep coming. I have knives enough for everyone."
A Thran relic, it has spent ten thousand years doing absolutely nothing.
"I will protect the less fortunate. I will love bravely. I will face despair and fight on. As a Capashen, I can do no less."
No ancient lore ties the pirates of the Brazen Coalition to the Immortal Sun. But it's a powerful ancient artifact in a city of gold—what's not to covet?
"They'll never see me coming."
"I have pustules of the great Ratadrabik, very cheap. No? Surely you'll want a tincture of Nevinyrral's pulverized remains. Genuine!"
"I've seen your house, and you've been a lovely, if unwitting, host. But at last it's time for farewells."
Eyes are unnecessary for seeing the future.
"Your mind is no longer yours to waste."
Demons lurk in the shadows of ancient ruins, spreading plague and corruption across the land.
The Benalish aristocracy is hereditary, but the loyalty of its subjects is earned.
"Go swiftly, clever arrow, and teach The philosophy of stillness." —D'Avenant verse

"To wage war, secure peace within yourself."
—Emmara
"May the light shine through me to guide the lost."
"Keep your friends close and your enemies within range."
"Welcome aboard, mate! You're going to need this."
"Up you go, you soggy rat."
Despite their noble heritage, the pirates of the Deadeye Fleet are known for underhanded tactics and despicable trickery.
You're only as dead as you feel.
All things considered, his first day on patrol could have gone better.

"Commander, what's the signal to attack?"
"You'll know."
For the necromancer barons, killing and recruitment are one and the same.
"Nature is not always gentle or kind, but all life begets life." —Marwyn of Llanowar
"Ancient one, we have reached the promised shore. The Immortal Sun is near. Drink and awake."
By design, the sarcophagus muffles the debtors' moans but does not silence them.

"If you think yourself a chief, then prove your might."
—Gar-Tun, Mistvalley silverback
For cryomancers, studying the Ice Age isn't just an academic exercise.
"No good will come from what you seek. Turn back now or suffer an ignoble death far from your home."
"You think I stand alone? I have the forest at my call, the waters at my back. I outnumber you."
"We breathe from our soul and bones to give strength to the jungle. The jungle breathes from its roots and rivers to give strength to us." —Shaper Falani
A visit to the Deeproot Tree and its ancient spring replenishes a merfolk's connection to nature.

"Leave no stone unturned."
—Ruric Thar
A knight's devotion to their steed goes only so far.
What took months for human hands to carve took just seconds for the dinosaur's tail to ruin.
In the Cabal, death is just another mark of devotion.
A pit yawned open, a column of oily smoke arose, and a towering form hissed, "I accept this offering."
There's no greater honor than joining your chosen guild, and no greater shame than failing it.
"The River Heralds carve spells into jade, hoping to steer us from our course. But what right do they have to keep us from that which once was ours?"

flavor_text: Pockets full of gold, lungs full of brine.
The grave robbers were startled, for the door to the mausoleum was already open.
A pirate crew without a ship is a crew that will do anything to get one.
Its light exposes enemies and lays secrets bare.
First, dispose of the evidence. Then dispose of your knowledge of the disposal.
"This is Mileva, in the Tenth. We've got an elf in the plaza with a chip on her shoulder. Actually, it's more of a morningstar."
When it passes, rainbows follow.
Archaeologists don't just dig in the dirt. They excavate time, scraping off the years grain by grain.

"Every guild dreads infiltration. I should know—I've been a member of all of them."
—Lazav
The letters arrive, all sealed and read.

"Wear this, and take your place among the shadows—wise, lethal, and unseen."
—Ivrelya, Dimir spymaster
Just assume every conversation is on record.
"Aye, the foul beast chomped me, but I got away. You'd best believe when I find it again, it won't get away so easy."
If you're in the way of a ceratops charge and you're made of mere flesh and bone, then you're not really in the way.
Orcs are happiest under captains who steer toward battle. Orcs of the Dire Fleet are downright jovial.
Among the pirates of the Brazen Coalition, the only thing more dangerous than failure is success.
The buccaneers scaled the sides of buildings as easily as they boarded enemy ships.
His fists fume with the decay of death, each strike a plague on the hearts of his enemies.

"At least this one still has arms and legs. Well, most of its legs."
—Enslow, ghoulcaller of Nephalia

flavor_text: "Laws apply only to those who lack the vision to see past them."

"People would sooner savor sweet lies than chew plain truths."
—Lazav
"Burn. Burn. Keep. Burn".
It's pointless to hold on when you have nothing to hold on with.
"The route is direct but challenging. Incidentally, how are you with heights?"
"Seeing the river is not the same as seeing the fish."
Flittersprites collect unusually valuable things: coins of fallen empires, baby teeth, and memories of treasured names.
"The stars mark your destiny. May you accept the fate thus divulged."
Cunning warriors and dim-witted beasts alike fall under the church's harsh judgment.
The angels appreciated the offer but politely declined to eat any birdseed.
"Good girl."
There is only one fate left to those banished from the God-Pharaoh's city.
The sound of every twisted secret tempts you to hear another.
First the insult, then the encore.

The party of Rakdos revelers cackled and capered as the thing approached. It hissed, and they jabbed their torches at it, giggling when it recoiled. Then, one by one, the torches went out—and the screaming began.
Dovin ticked the Planeswalkers off on his fingers: himself, Domri, Kaya, Ral, Vraska . . . and Bolas made an even six.
It was made for battle, but that doesn't mean it's unsophisticated.
"We're finished here."

flavor_text: "If I am to die, I will die in the embrace of an immeasurable flame."
Dragon birth lairs are littered with treasure to entice the young from their eggs.
When the Planeswalker Angrath called dinosaurs "dragons," the name stuck in certain pirate circles.
"The forest surrounding the Vess estate became the Caligo Morass, a vast bog stalked by horrors too terrible to name." — "The Fall of the House of Vess"
Never boring.
"I do not lead. They do not follow. We walk together."
None can tell how many vessels are tangled up on the sea floor—or how much treasure remains unclaimed.
Beneath Ravnica's streets runs a layer of tunnels, then caverns, then waterways, then terrors and nightmares.
The Cabal assured the Seven Houses that hostages receive all the food and rest they require.
No welcome for those who trespass. Only fang and horn and claw.
"The wild tangle of the Cowl provides sanctuary to life that watched the first buildings rise."
"The land already knows its destiny. I simply ask it to share the tale with me."
"Through me the rage of Tilonalli burns twice as bright."
"Rise, knight of New Benalia."

"It hurts more if you think about it."
—Hooks, Cabal torturer
"The hour of Dusk is come."
Stories say demon blood runs in its veins, making it fearless and bloodthirsty.
It loomed up over the horizon, silent and dark as a grave.
Once they reached Orazca, the Legion's explorers ransacked tombs and temples, hunting for the Immortal Sun.
"These storied halls are under my protection."
The collection didn't have room to expand, so the wizard improvised a solution.
"Some hid from the storm. I embraced it and learned its name."
"Basically, we turn a bunch of little lightnings into one big lightning."

"It's both an ingress-denial mechanism and an attractive hallway light!"
—Daxiver, Izzet electromancer
Her centuries-long search is ended.
The bond between Llanowar elves and their kavu empowers both.
"Hold it! I need to see your papers."
No single root feeds the forest.
"By accepting my smallness I am vast."
"Whatever hatred destroys, a single act of trust can revive."
Paladins of the Sanctum Seeker order are an adventurous lot, venturing into the wilds with monstrous mastiffs at their side.

"Smash this city to pieces."
—Domri Rade

"Who are the agents of the Dimir? No one and everyone."
—Lazav
Many initiates believe it possesses secrets beyond imagining. Many have become meals trying to learn them.
"There's no time to calm it down! Run!"
The stronger the will, the more bewitching the song.
"Fleshy, with just a hint of leather. A fine vintage."

"The League accepts no responsibility for former members and the damage they may cause."
—Maree, Izzet chamberlain

"The Erstwhile—rotten of body and outmoded in dress, but unfailing in loyalty."
—Vraska

"It's not enough to defeat our foes. We must learn from them, too."
—Vannifar
Dependence on luck is anathema to Kefnet's rigorous studies. Those who hope to escape his maze by chance never succeed.
The storm rages and the earth breaks.

"Time to let the dead be dead."
—Kaya, to Teysa
"Undefeated in battle, she is the shining future our empire deserves." —Huatli
"Fear the dark if you must, but don't mistake sunlight for safety." —Josu Vess
The Sun Empire bends nature—rivers, mountainsides, dinosaurs—to its unyielding will.
"Light from the Null Moon took form—a mirage made real, alone in grandeur, isolated in a world that once had been its own." —Fall of the Thran
Successful battles start with knowing who's worth fighting.

flavor_text: Turns out coffee is the weird aunt of invention.

"Souls are volatile things. When compressed and loaded into a handheld device, their destructive potential is quite impressive."
—Dierk, geistmage

"Lies cannot long withstand the harsh light of day."
—Lavinia
"We have come at last to this holiest of holy places. What was stolen from us long ago is ours once again."
"They've got eyes inside my head!"
Faeries are easily offended and quick to exact a quirky revenge.
Loyal to his queen, slave to his thirst.
"The Brazen Coalition is a firecannon pointed at our enemies. Goblins like him are the spark to its powder." —Admiral Beckett Brass
Without frequent raids, orcs sometimes get bored and plunder their own ships.
"Join me, and take the world for yourself!"
"It was a bad evening for you, mate. Now it's chow time for the sharks."
As she charges into battle, her arcane tattoos stir and crawl like fiery serpents.
"Like ribbons of wind and wisdom the coatls fly, twisting mystery into truth, shaping the clouds to suit their inscrutable will." —Huatli
"I spent some time in the Legion, but I'm done taking orders all day."
"Urborg used to be lovely—scenic volcanoes, respectable lich lords. Since the Cabal came with their nightmares and thrulls, it's all gone to the worms." —Mister Lostspoons, Skulltown gossip.

"Lost are the lush meadows and verdant forests, where maaka prowled and lammasu soared. Lost are the wilds, where our hearts were free."
—Daiva, Gruul storyteller
"The flame paints a bright wheel on the sky, then shifts into a stabbing spark. The enemy falls; the smoke of victory rises. — "Legends of the Firedancer"
As it walks across the fallow field, its awkward, loping gait matches the rattling in its head to create a haunting rhythm that chills the bones.
Wary of the ferocious dinosaurs, the Legion of Dusk built up the walls of their fort—just in time for the pirates to burn them down.
Negotiations reached an abrupt conclusion.
Burning something is easy. Choosing a target can be more difficult.
"Sleep now, brother. That is the one gift I can give you." —Liliana Vess
There's nothing quite like the feeling of paying off a large debt.

flavor_text: "Let's find out what kind of audience you are. Festive? Fearless?"
Goblins' fearlessness and diminutive size make them the perfect cannoneers.
It treads on feet of coals and strikes with the force of a volcano.
The versatile "fiery gauntlet" is among the first spells young Ghitu mages learn.
Though grimed with the dust of centuries, the ancient shrine was not unguarded.
The peaks of Hurloon never fall silent.
Rain runoff in the Smelting District is known to spontaneously burst into flame.
"Fire will cure a multitude of ills."
"Captain, I think that island is following us."
"Yes, there's competition between our equenauts and the Boros skyjeks. At least they think it's a competition."
Jace tumbled down the waterfall and plunged deep into his past.

flavor_text:
"No worthwhile reward is easily gained."
—Nicol Bolas

"This footlight's broken. Get me a stagehand!"
—Judith
"You will respect the dead."

"Prayers will curdle on the tongue and be heard by rotting ears."
—Minaldra, the Vizag Atum
The stench of rotting meat lures flies, goblins, and young raptors.
Entrepreneurs have attempted to sell the water, but to no avail. Whatever magic it contains disappears upon bottling.
The Great Mending that healed the Multiverse also unraveled the threads of Nicol Bolas's power.
"The heat in our hearts sometimes rises to the surface." — Valduk, keeper of the Flame.
Sun Empire warriors are taught to emulate the fearless raptors that fling themselves against towers of horn and muscle a hundred times their size.

"Hold on to your ideals. They'll be tested more than your armor or the edge of your blade."
—Tajic
Nothing says trouble like a reedy hiss with a hint of liquid gurgle.
"Your arrival was expected...and unwelcome."

"Reel it in. No, wait! Throw it back!"
—Gertrude, deep-sea angler
To thallids, the whole world is just a pile of mulch to grow saprolings in.
Thallids nurture saprolings, entertain them, and eat them.
Fallen Phyrexians were transmuted into elementals by Gaea long ago, but Yavimaya's other inhabitants still regard them with unease.
"Our duty does not stop at our borders."

"I might have overfed him."
—Gulistan, Simic biomancer

"Do not mistake a quiet rampart for one that is unguarded. Some things stir only when they need to."
—Bonovar, siege commander
In the Legion, no flagpole is merely decorative, and every ceremonial sword bears an edge.
So-called "battering rams" pale in comparison to the real thing.
Each night it visits a different guildgate around the city, digging its talons into fresh stone.
When the Izzet's spirit of invention extends to the city's infrastructure, the results are sometimes explosive.
The Chamber of the Guildpact has fallen silent, its bright promise broken.
"I've been through every guild gate in this city, and no one sees me come or go."
Made in its creator's image, though slightly more clangy.
Young artificers on Kaladesh let their imaginations run wild.
Cats place their gifts with care, so that a bare foot will step on them in the middle of the night.

"Vraska sees the grandeur in death but misses the hilarity."
—Judith
The earth walks, strongest of all.
They grow closer with every passing season.
Fairgoers were delighted to find that even outside the fairgrounds, Ghirapur was a city of wonders.
"What fire forged, fire remembers."
The Ghitu of Shiv are as fierce and uncompromising as their volcanic home.
Tolarians teach the theory of pyromancy. The Ghitu prefer applied research.
"Today the Rubblebelt is a bit larger. That's a good day's work."
"Picking locks is for beginners."

"After everything I've survived, it's hard to be frightened by anything anymore."
—Vivien Reid
On Amonkhet, Gideon lost both his sural and his faith in himself. But he can still throw a punch, and he still knows a bad guy when he sees one.

"When the sky screams, when the ground groans, the End-Raze will soon begin."
—Nikya of the Old Ways

"Each tooth is the length of a horse, and new ones grow in every sixteen days. Let's get a closer look!"
—Vivien Reid
"The perfection of the lotus reminds me of my hopes for this world . . . and my failures. I will not rest until I've atoned for them." —Karn
The River Heralds fight to keep all others from reaching the golden city. The city has its own defenses.
"The only gold I need is the sheltering shimmer of the trees."

"You won't need the sword drills, your shields, or my blessing. You'll fight for Sunhome with the truth in your heart."
—Aurelia
Ships blown north in their voyage across the Stormwreck Sea become trapped in the unmelting ice.

"Counterbalanced forces sustain this city. No faction above others. A beautiful idea."
—Emmara
"Gold without freedom might as well be lead." —Angrath
"The blood of the enemy is a sacrament. The strength it gives is proof that our cause is just."
From death she grows living grandeur.
The Boros banner stands tall even if its bearer doesn't.
"The trick is, once you get moving, don't stop!"

"Result 752: Rapid mass redistribution.
"Result 753: Calamitous reverse synthesis.
"Result 754: Acute disarrayment."
—Izzet research notes
Two's a party. Three's a felony.
"We can take 'em. You go first!"

"He's got more finesse than most goblins. He smashes windows with his fist rather than his forehead."
—Arrester Polgar
Small words stoke large flames.
"Why are we following the goblin? Can he even read that map?" —Daphne Vail, Diremore first mate
"Folks 'round here are too in love with their contraptions. Does them some good if we smash every one so often."
Not since the days of Pashalik Mons have the Rundvelt goblins been so united or effective.
Sin is debt, and absolution is paid in tithes of gold and blood.

flavor_text: "We gather the past from surface dwellers and sell it right back to them."

"Shut the gates. In the Underrealm we will outlast the coming doom."
—Vraska

"Wear it at all times. It will guide our reanimators to your corpse."
—Mazirek, kraul death priest
What the Golgari can't claim through patient undercity expansion, they seize in brazen topside sorties.
You don't want to know how she got that name.
"Follow her footsteps and she will show you the way." —Itzama the Crested
"The future is my gift to Keld."
Some rooftop gardens attract bees; others capture dragons.
"I can hear the plunder calling. It asks for me by name."
"Debt due! Debt due!" The thrull's screeching makes children flinch and debtors quail. "Debt due!"
A full coffin is like a full coffer—both are attractive to thieves.

"No peace accord will save Ravnica. You don't build on rot. You burn it down and start again."
—Domri Rade
Once every seven years it flies on spectral wings over the moors of ancient battlefields.

"Rise and shine, my dears. We have work to do."
—Isareth the Awakener
Often found browsing on the upper canopies of Ixalan's jungles, whiptails are known to absently bat away anything foolish enough to interrupt their meal.
Within a mile of the woodland, you will feel her eyes upon you. Within its borders, you will feel her blade.
When the battle is over, the bitterest foes at last find common ground.

"A debtor's soul has little value, except as a warning to others who might consider defaulting on their loans."
—Ubea, Orzhov ministrant

flavor_text: Cyclical and spiral patterns are the specialty of the Gyre Clade, which seeks to revitalize the cycles of nature.
"You were keen enough to sink your fangs into us, vampire! And now you're afraid of a few little nibbles?" —Udvil "Ratty" Ratlock

"Variety is also the spice of death."
—Cevraya, Golgari shaman

"Beyond this gate there are no citizens, only predators and prey."
—Domri Rade

"In life, it was a cunning survivor, fearless and quick. May its power pass to you as you wear its skull."
—Gna, Gruul shaman
She displays her scars with pride.
Simic's strength comes from its diversity.
Archaeologists depend on automatons inspired by their precious discoveries at Koilos to guard the excavations.
In a climate of suspicion, Isperia gathered the guilds to propose a radical idea: cooperation.

"Down here, things don't stay dead."
—Lavinia
"I found a new toy. Wanna play?"
"As I contemplate what is, I dive ever deeper into the depths of possibility. Then I set an experiment in motion and watch the truth rise to the surface."
Ravnica's convoluted power structure often boils down to who can muster the most swords on a given block.
"You two, cover the alley! You, with me! Eyes on windows, balconies, and rooftops. Who knows what a fish-octopus-crab can do!"
"They all want to see me fall."

flavor_text: The ever-watchful center of a growing web of eyes.
Giants know a solid hit is one part strength, four parts leverage.
For the Sun Empire, the Immortal Sun is a symbol of national identity. When they reclaim it, the Empire will flourish once more.
For devils, burning things is the highest form of comedy, diversion, and artistic expression.
"Watch your backs, keep your blades at hand, and let the orc go first!" —Captain Brandis Thorn
"The elders say that if the intruders discovered the secret of the golden city, it would mean an end to our people."
The wounded see the glow of its vials long before they see its wings diving out of the clouds.
"Whatever faith you have in Serra, she has more in you." —Lyra Dawnbringer

"They play by spitting fire at each other. Don't be offended if one gives you a love-scorch."
—Esfir, Rakdos dragon wrangler
Forged out of flowstone for the queen of Vesuva.
The clerics prayed for salvation. The soldiers prayed for victory. Both prayers were answered.
"You might as well try to stop the waterfall."
Cries of anguish quickly spurred cries of action.
When the established order falters, what remains are ordinary people and their struggle to survive.
Law protects but it also contains.
In the Rite of Redemption, nobles take the same vows as Elenda, the first vampire, and make the same eternal sacrifice.

"Bring down a stag and fix its horns upon Arel's head. She hears the wisdom of our ancestors."
—Chianul, Who Whispers Twice

"A place like this makes me wonder if there's more to life than blood and treasure . . . Nah."
—Boyl Bucksalt, Storm Fleet swab
Trapped on Ixalan, the Planeswalker Angrath is the only minotaur sailing the seas. No matter how many ships he captures, he cannot break free.
"Our ancestors brought down a Phyrexian portal ship, then built our town on its hull. We're pretty proud of that." —Alene of Riverspan
"If you want them dead, buy some poison. If you want them to have the worst day of their life before dying, then let's talk price."
"They don't even feel the cut. I'm ordering a drink in a nearby tavern before anyone notices something's wrong."
Nearly invisible strands of web reach for beyond its lair to alert it of the approach of prey.
"Homarids spread northward from Sarpadia as the climate cooled, raiding coastal settlements for supplies." — Time of Ice
Being a merciful pirate, she saved the vampire's gold from falling overboard.
The bellow of minotaur always translates to "charge."
It wails of buried riches and the souls lost seeking them.
Don't make the mistake of thinking blunt horns can't kill.
"Run like the wind, fierce one. The hunt has begun."
Searching the city for Fblthp felt like sifting the rain for a single drop of blood.
He ferried weapons, spells, exotic animals—but his most dangerous cargo was the truth.
"Death lizard approaching, cap'n!" —Brint Doobin, last words
Havoc is a small price to pay for data.

"It's like blowing up an arcane library in a thermobaric explosion. But in a good way."
—Bori Andon, Izzet blastseeker
Ice may thaw, but malice never does.
"The suffering of others is not my concern."
"Hello, kindling."
Never let the glitter of gold distract you from the gleam of steel in the shadows.
In times of unrest, the crowd is eager for the comfort of strong convictions.
Its assistance is unnervingly similar to its hunting technique.
"The music of blades against its silver armor merely inspires it to bellow more full-throated melodies." —Huatli
"Together my mount and I are stronger than either of us apart."
The rights of ghosts are strictly protected under Orzhov bylaws, and those who enforce them can count on the ghosts' assistance.
The ultimate answer to intrigue and subtlety.
"Your contract is in default. You belong to me now. Serve, or die." — Nicol Bolas

flavor_text:
"The Izzet are blamed for every little disaster, which is unfair because we only cause most of them."
— Mizzix of the Izmagnus
Not once in the history of Grixis has anyone died of old age.
"When these intruders are gone, Zendikar will be my throne, my palace, my playground."
One who is marked by a demon in life is sure to be remembered as one in death.
"Impossible! How could they overwhelm us? We had barricades, war elephants, … and they were barely a tenth of our number!" —General Avitora
"The Immortal Sun will bring us true eternal life to replace the everlasting shadow of undeath."
There are two lives: The life you live before you see a unicorn, and the life you live after.

card_faces: [{'object': 'card_face', 'name': 'Integrity', 'mana_cost': '{R/W}', 'type_line': 'Instant', 'oracle_text': 'Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.', 'watermark': 'boros', 'artist': 'Ben Maier', 'illustration_id': 'd0925ff9-0837-4934-b3d9-c62fdcb3be78'}, {'object': 'card_face', 'name': 'Intervention', 'mana_cost': '{2}{R}{W}', 'type_line': 'Instant', 'oracle_text': 'Intervention deals 3 damage to any target and you gain 3 life.', 'watermark': 'boros', 'artist': 'Ben Maier'}]

flavor_text: Good at carrying things. Really good at knocking them down.

flavor_text:
"Let go of all that harms you. Cast your burdens into the darkness, and build for the faithful a house of light."
—Song of All, canto 1008
"Countermagic is a simple process of breaking matter into its elementary particles."

"Please don't feed the beetles."
—Promenade warning sign
Threefold were his crimes, doubled were his pleas, singular was his fate.
Serra's blessing lies strongest upon Sursi, where her holy chapels are untouched even as the Cabal encroaches.
Jace awoke to the certainty that he was lost.
The people of the Sun Empire worship the sun in three aspects. Ixalli is the Verdant Sun, who fosters growth in all things.
Every laboratory buzzes with new experiments, each a piece of Ral's ambitious project.

"Remember to discharge your locket every seven hours. Unless you prefer the spontaneous aether overload, of course."
—Daxiver, Izzet electromancer
"We drove the Sun Empire out of the forest long ago, and we will not let them return."
"Sisora wore this, who defeated the tyrant of Azcanta, and before her Natena of Vuhana's band. May it bring you their strength."
"A blade is not fully forged until it is given."
The River Heralds believe that jade gives weight to their magic.
Centuries ago, a pyromancer's spark ignited a fiery conflagration.
"You could say it was my pet project." —Jhoira
As she took the wheel of the Weatherlight for the first time in a millennium, Jhoira knew she'd been right to restore the ship. Anything was possible now.
"Chronicles across the ages describe Jodah. They likely refer not to one mage, but to a family or an arcane title." — Arkol, Argivian scholar
"We are the shield that never breaks, the bough that never burns, the song that can never be silenced."

flavor_text: At the end of the show, she stands alone on a stage brilliant with blood.
"Urza's machines have a splendid habit of excavating themselves." — Rona, disciple of Gix
"We fought so long to hide this place. Let us be first to learn its wonders!"
"You cannot kill it, not for long. It ripens where the ground is soaked with the blood of the slaughtered." —Atiuru, priest of the Verdant Sun
"There is no power too great to be used in the defense of our ancestral lands."

"Hey, wait! That's my boot!"
—Darijo, Ivy Street ruffian

"Those who show no mercy to the weak deserve no mercy from the strong."
—Firemane Kavrova
With the new guildmaster's innovations, arresters can arrive on the scene moments before a crime is committed.
Centuries ago, a barbarian laid his rage to rest.
"Only those who give the dragons the respect they deserve may bear our title."
Centuries ago, a quest to harness time became a spiral into chaos.
"Don't worry, they won't bite. They much prefer setting people on fire." — Jaya Ballard, to Chandra
Teysa convened the meeting of the Obzedat. Kaya ended it.
Keldon raiders' spoils are limited to what their colos can carry. No matter the value, the rest goes up in smoke.
"The Mountain gave us the Flame to Kradak to light the furnaces of his people's hearts. The wanderers became Keldons, and he the first warlord." — "The Flame of Keld"
The people of the Sun Empire worship the sun in three aspects. Kinjalli is the Wakening Sun, who created humans from clay and baked them in the sun's warmth.
"There are moments when I feel I could fly like the sunwing. Far away I would soar, but always a golden gale pushes me back." —Huatli
"Why perch in the crow's nest when I can fly like the crows?"
A light to pierce the shadows.
A shadow to swallow the light.

The mage-smiths of New Benalia have perfected the art of blending fine steel and enchanted glass into weapons that are both beautiful and deadly. Only elite knights are entrusted with these martial works of art.
The helmet reveals no eyes to witness your penance, no mouth to offer absolution.
"My whisper becomes a thousand roars."
"Horse? Who needs a horse?"
"As long as my faith persists, so shall I."
"I know these waters better than you know yourselves."

Feed on food, you eventually rot. Feed on rot, you live forever.
—Kraul saying
The kraul once skulked in the outskirts of Golgari society, but with Vraska's rise, the became valued forces of the Swarm.
The hive has a long memory. It knows how every member has died, and tow home it owes the grudge.
"Druids endure disaster as seeds endure winter. Now Krosa blooms once more."
"The same power that drives the river ever onward flows through the roots and branches—to me."
Descendant of a vanished land, student of a forgotten general, and master of blades no smith could forge anew. He honors them all by living a life worthy of song.
"Catch!"

"Commander, we caught the Dimir spy and took her ashes into custody."
—Kramm, Wojek security officer
"I told Jace that Ravnica would fall apart if he didn't take his responsibilities seriously. I didn't want to be right."

"Most compete for insects at street level. Some dwell near Izzet laboratories and ride the thermal updrafts."
—Yolov, Simic bioengineer.
"I've raised her since she was a pup, and she's raised me since I was a recruit."
The Legion of Dusk sailed from Torrezon in search of glory, riches, and the Immortal Sun.
"We long ago abandoned the things that make humans weak: friendship, marriage, family. All that remains is the strength of our devotion."
"My lance was once wielded by Venerable Tarrian. In his name and by his might, I cast you down!"

flavor_text: "Those who do evil and those who do nothing are equally worthy of contempt."
The best fighters are skilled in both harming and healing.
When one leonin hunts, many more are surely nearby.
A lich must consume mortal souls to feed its eternal life.
When it passes, storm clouds bolt across the land.
A pirate ship in battle is a storm of activity.
To wield lightning is to tame chaos.

"Places, everyone!"
—Judith
Immortality is worth any price.
"True power never dies, but lies awake, waiting for its name to be spoken." — The Eldest Reborn
As patient and generous as life, as harsh and merciless as nature.
"Cherish this world in honor of the martyrs who saved it. We too must be prepared to give our lives." — The Mending of Dominaria
Llanowar elfhames occupy different heights within the great forest. Elves of the Loridalh and Kelfae hames can see neither earth nor sky.
Her song plucks the strings of the storm, shifting wind and storm into a harmony that will carry her ship to safety.
Nature can't be tamed, but the Sun Empire believes that humans are made stronger when they test themselves against the wild strength of the dinosaurs.

"I prefer the big and looming to the small and skittering."
—Cevraya, Golgari shaman
Loxodons are firm in stature and spirit. No matter the odds, they are always first into battle.

"Article 5.8.2. Ensure proper restraint of any and all arms, legs, claws, jaws, tails, tentacles, and tendrils as appropriate."
—*Azorius Arrester Procedure*, Appendix B.
"Shadow birthed it. The moon gave it eyes, and the jungle gave it teeth. But it was Death that taught it cruelty." —Huatli
"You are not alone. You never were."
The Rakdos put the "fun" in "funeral."
Liliana is never one to follow someone else's lead.
"Its rise is like the sun's, a beautiful beginning. Its descent is like the sun's, a frightful ending." —Huatli
For a moment they stood tall, all fear forgotten.
"Grease up a firecannon good and proper with dinosaur-liver oil, and it'll shoot just about anything."

"The good news is that the migrating drakes are no longer a problem."
—Bell Migellic, Azorius hussar
Planeswalkers seek out great monuments throughout the Multiverse, knowing that their builders were unknowingly drawn by the convergence of mana in the area.

"They tell us the wilds are ours, then they brick them over. They can lie to our faces but not to our fists."
—Ghut Rak, Gruul guildmage
A sharp axe solves most problems.
"I'll be taking that."
"Our forces number more than the leaves of Vitu-Ghazi. Do not provoke us."
"Through your sacrifice of self, you become holy. Through your strength, all will be saved." —From the Rite of Redemption
"Should I fall, take up our standard and carry on. The Legion must always prevail."
Midwife to mothers and leader to all.
Those who cross the Dimir find enemies everywhere they turn.
Another piece of a nefarious puzzle.
In the rapture of his Blood Fast, he destroyed the navigator's tools and steered the ship to shore by faith alone.
The river split into many channels as it flowed to the Halimar Sea. Few travelers could follow the same one twice.
"In these halls there is no pass or fail. Your true test comes with the first full moon."
Ravnica's safest strongholds are often neither.
"The mist clothes us when we are bare, hides us when we are alone, and unites us when we are together." —Nirit of Pashona's band
Saved from destruction by one planeswalker's sacrifice, the Eliterate colony forswore the taking of life.
The unicorns of Sursi are a manifestation of Serra's joy and compassion. They frolic and dance like children, offering blessings to anyone they encounter.
The impact sent the soldiers scattering—then something came out of the crater.
No one welcomes his visit, yet all must grant him tribute.

"There is nothing stronger than many hearts united for a single cause."
—Emmara
"I feel the presence of the God-Pharaoh in the Second Sun, and I rise upon its rays."
Minds, like mountains, are never so grand and mighty that they can't be reduced to dust.
Many an inventor has collapsed under the pressure to create a flawless design.
When the price of your sins comes due, the Church of Deals is there to collect.
The life of a shapeshifter is one of constant change.
It has witnessed history's most significant events, one incarnation after another.
Hospitality is of little concern to those who do not wish to be disturbed.
With matchless stealth, the River Heralds fought a running battle against the three enemy forces.
"The time of condemnation is at hand. Dusk washes over the world, and I consign you to eternal darkness!"
"The time of salvation is at hand. Dusk washes over the world, and the Legion will rise immortal!"

"Your debt is erased."
—Hilgur, Orzhov euthanist
A moment in time made tangible, it has the power to realize epic visions.

"My child grew from rot and ruin, yet she bloomed."
—Multani
"It's not work if you enjoy it."
Rumors float through the city like crows, alighting on citizens seemingly at random.
A composer wrote a symphony based on the drakes screeching outside her window. Reviews were mixed—except among the drakes.
Pirate captains rarely enjoy a peaceful retirement.
The delight of discovery drives the pursuit of knowledge.
"Perfect. Now do it again."

"What bait do you cast to catch a dream?"
—Ravnican riddle

"And if you threaten me again, your shiny steel trousers will be sprouting daggerthorn vines."
—Iveta, rooftop runner
"As Argoth's last defenders fell to Urza's juggernauts, Titania said, 'Nature cannot be destroyed, only changed.'" —The Antiquities War
The Weatherlight can no longer planeshift, but it can traverse Dominaria with ease.
"You won't be needing this. Or this. Or these . . ."
The assassins of Ochran distill toxins from the remains of the previous victims.
It hatches with its ferocity fully grown.
"As one, nature lifts its voice to tell you this: 'No.'"
"These sailors on our shores are like the dinosaurs that plunder eggs from nests. They live on the labors of others." —Itzama the Crested
Dimir assassins have the precision to slay a single memory.
Sarkhan wandered into a tomb and back in time.
"My father will be happy to see you."

flavor_text: That feeling of something on your chest is usually sleep paralysis. Occasionally, it's something else.

"Three daggers left in an angel's back, three enforcers with memory loss, three keys stolen from my own belt—and you talk of peace?"
—Tajic, to Aurelia

"We're on the fortieth floor, with one window, no balcony. No one could possibly get in."
—Minosz, Orzhov chief of security
"The hooves of the Raze-Bore will trample the weak—and their city—to dust!"
City air is a constant drizzle of private thoughts.
Even the greatest hero begins with nothing.

"Behold the groodion! Ichor-slurper, oozing fiend. Foulest wonder underground. Grandest vermin of them all!"
—Zalin the Gutter Bard

"When the beast cloaks itself in the mighty oak, what good is a bow? When the oak wraps itself around the snarling beast, what good is a hatchet?"
—Dionus, elvish archdruid
"For the lost and forgotten, I will keep watch."
"My conquistadors are never slain, merely laid to rest." —Queen Miralda the Pious
"The dagger is just a distraction. I carry the real killer in a vial at my side."
"The jungle was here before any city. It will be here after the last city falls."
Her prophecies amaze her even as she speaks them.

"The things I once imagined would be my greatest achievements were only the first steps toward a future I can only begin to fathom."
— Jace Beleren
She memorized every arcane text in the Ismeri Library by the time she was sixteen. Now she quizzes sphinxes in her spare time.
The ogres you know are nothing like the Onakke. Possessing both intellect and industry, they had brute strength without being brutish.

"When I grafted the Planar Bridge into myself, I felt my Planeswalker spark flare beyond my body. The Multiverse was my plaything. It felt . . . incredible."
—Tezzeret
"River and sea, jungle and sky. Water flows freely between the two halves of the world. We are creatures of the water." —Shaper Tuvasa
"The spirit of Serra raised Brindri high and commanded her to keep the balance." —Song of All, canto 524

"If you don't have a destination in mind, the route is all that matters."
—Tamina, district guide
It was a night like any other. It would soon become a night no one would ever forget.
The crystal pulsed with the power of Teferi's planeswalker spark. Had Jhoira given him a blessing or a curse?
The frillbacks of Orazca soak up the sun on their tall spinal fins. They look slow and sleepy—until they catch the scent of prey.
"If you come across a raptor in the city, stay perfectly still. At least then you'll be well rested when you die." —Captain Brandis Thorn
Every ancient relic is a weapon if you throw it hard enough.
The leonin of Oreskos are quick to take offense—not because they are thin-skinned but because they are always ready for a fight.
"Nobody ever listens to my complaints! Not even when I use the listening stick."
"You'll pay what you owe, with your money or your life."

"So much wealth. So much splendor. So much temptation to believe the gilded lie."
—Kaya

"It looks expensive, doesn't it? You have no idea..."
—Milana, Orzhov prelate
"Looks like you need protection."
"Forward! Let the Burning Sun's light guide you to deserving prey!"
The truth came to Kumena like the Great River's torrent: the only way to keep his enemies away from the hidden city was to claim its power for himself.
It embodies the riotous growth of the jungle, where creatures crowd upon creatures, where roots sprawl and vines swarm.
Cradle of the Golgari's new kingdom. Grave of those who wronged its queen.
Selesnya grows its ranks in more ways than one.
For every wound there is a blessing; for every death, a reckoning.
Closely linked to the Church of Dusk, the paladins of the Bloodstained order are devout to the point of fanaticism.
Sister of Nicol Bolas. Survivor of the Elder Dragon War. The most vicious of her kin.
"To the head of Archaeological Findings: The excavation schedule at dig site 93-beta must be revised. Part of the site has walked off." —Tolarian field dispatch
"Too many have disappeared in these dark days. I am the light that will lead them home."
"My doors are called trespassing, my signatures, forgeries. They don't respect my talents, and I don't respect their labels."

artist: Victor Adame Minguez & Victor Adame Minguez

flavor_text: Nicol Bolas would not rest until he was restored to his former glory.
A pegasus chooses its rider, bearing the worthy into the clouds and tossing all others to the ground.
It eats what it wants to eat—which is anything that moves.
Its elaborate designs reveal secrets of aether's flow.
For the first time in her life, Vraska tried to prevent death.
Its stench corrodes steel. Its miasma sickens angels. Its finality ends hope.
Llanowar elves conceal their ballistae in the upper canopy of the forest, ready to clear the skies of any intruder.
"Ours is the true and righteous path. You will bow before our might."
Goblins can carry their body weight in loot.
Nothing warms the heart like plunder.
Its hyperpneumatics can punch through a wall and the spy on the other side.
"The reign of the Swarm begins. Let us rise now and dress ourselves in vengeance."
"Shame to let good gold go to the grave."
"Pay in gold. Pay in blood. Pay with the servitude of your spirit kin. But pay you must."
"My power is generosity, in a way. I give my survivors an appreciation for their lives."
When it passes, those who sleep dream of sickness and death.
For some goods, the best couriers are the dead.

"Let nothing own the skies but the wind."
—Dejara, Giltwood druid
An innumerable pack is concealed in a single reflection.
Nature's way of saying "take the long way home."
The drive to hunt and feed is raw instinct for dinosaurs. The trick is simply to channel it in the right direction.
"Light passing through a powerstone is refracted by eternity and colored by planar energy. I wonder how the world appeared through Urza's eyes?" — Teferi
Ral had wielded lightning all his life but had never harnessed the power of an entire guild.
"To control the present we must master the future."

"Light up the dark to find your way, and the dark may seek you out."
—Zalin the Gutter Bard
The Orzhov are not the only religious tradition on Ravnica, nor the oldest.

flavor_text: Centuries ago, five dragons conquered death to rule the living.
"You can hear its tail thrashing from a mile away. Keep in mind that its jaws may already be half a mile closer." — Jenson Carthalion, Yavimaya exile

"Look at how cute it is now!"
—Vivien Reid

artist: Bastien L. Deharme & Bastien L. Deharme

flavor_text: The floating city of High and Dry hasn't yet sunk under the weight of gold, but it's not for want of trying.
Imitation is the sincerest form of piracy.
A hunter in the city requires the utmost cunning to survive. It must pounce only if the kill is certain, and leave the remains where no one will see.
"Citizen! Your crime has been recorded. Cease movement and await arrest, or further penalties will be immediately imposed."

"To break another's mind is to deliver a fate worse than death. It is a terrifying power."
—Jace Beleren
"I turn around and see nothing, yet I know it is behind me. Its fingers rummage in my mind, crafting new ideas."
"To rise like the sun—there is no greater feeling."
"From the volcanoes of Shiv to the Balduvian steppes, I have sought a worthy teacher. At last, I have found one."
"My greatest creation—me!"
The soldiers of the Legion of Dusk have come to the colonies at Queen's Bay in search of glory and riches. They are veterans of centuries of warfare, and they thirst for conquest.
"Let the blood of the impure flow through you. Only the blessings of the golden city will purge its acrid taste from your mouth." —High Marshal Arguel
"When properly invoked, the plasma globule encloses the offensive spell with a satisfying slurp.

"You should have seen the look on both their faces."
—Morkamp, Lambholt innkeeper
As the Cabal legions pushed into Shiv, they learned not to stand so close together.
Genius is finding the edge of what's possible, then jumping over it.
"Your precious laws can't save you now!"
Its breath is a gale. Its roar is a volcano. Its anger tears soul from flesh.
Carnivorous dinosaurs developed a taste for undead flesh, tracking the vampires by the scent of blood on their breath.
One was spared to tell the gruesome tale.
Ever wonder why you never see an old Rakdos Cultist?

"My servants take pains for your pleasure, and take pleasure in your pain!"
—Rakdos

"This trinket will gain you admittance to some painfully exclusive gatherings."
—Exava, blood witch

"That one has a bright future—perfect instincts for the rhythm of mayhem."
—Judith
"Entertain me."

"The louder their performance, the quieter we become in comparison. They are the perfect distractions, for only fools ignore the Rakdos."
—Lazav
"The sun's strength sings in our hearts! I have never been more proud of my home and my people." —Huatli
The guildmasters loom large in the political sphere, but in the end, the rulers of Ravnica are its people.
"Rage! Rage until the whole world burns!"
Keldon warriors take advantage of the cyclops's inability to focus on more than one thing at a time.
All raptors are aggressive, but ferocidons seem to enjoy their prey's pain.
"Be advised: suspect is nine stories tall, marble hair, answers to Saint Gusztav."
Tumult is its natural habitat.
They cover their territory like a tide of teeth and claws.
The abundance of foes in Orazca means the raptors no longer need any orders.
"Every little hatchling has a parent's claws to guard it." —Sun Empire saying
Wreckage from the Phyrexian Invasion provided the rats with a seemingly unlimited number of breeding grounds.
Opening Orazca unleashed more horrors than just the Immortal Sun.
A daggertooth's triumphant roar makes all the sounds of jungle life fall silent.
A harpy's hoard is a filthy, bloodstained pile of trinkets and corpses.

"They may show up with the wrong thigh bone or mandible, but they always show up."
—Zul Ashur, lich lord
Onora knew with sudden, grim certainty he would never see the Great River again.
"Hard to starboard! Starb— Abandon ship! Abandon ship!"
"What was once formed by masons, shaped by smiths, or given life by mages, I will return to the embrace of the earth."
"The bones of the past will tell their tales—if you know how to speak their language."
"No more fear of death's oblivion—is this not the greatest treasure of all?" —Gurezan, Legion resurrectionist
Those of esteemed birth earn a most esteemed death.

"When you get right down to it, the difference between death and life is just a membrane-enclosed environment maintained by a metabolic process."
—Gulistan, Simic biomancer
"Seeing a pack of these monsters hunt together, I'm at a loss to imagine the size of their prey." —Adrian Adanto of Lujio
"Here and gone like a fleeting breeze."
As the battle for Orazca unfolded, the contenders discovered that others had already staked a claim.
Her knack for tampering with wards got her kicked out of the academy, but they also got her back in.
The most holy treasures are kept far from unclean soil.
A lifetime of keeping up appearances is not enough to earn an eternity of rest.

flavor_text: With just a few seconds to escape, Deryan saved Hurkyl's editions on restoring physical objects from ash.
A friend in good times, a guardian in bad times, and a savior when all else fails.

flavor_text: "A potion is no substitute for a skilled surgeon, but it will hold your bits in." —Torricks, battlefield medic

flavor_text:
"The dead gain new purpose here. What is strange in the eyes of other guilds is harmonious in ours."
—Devesh, Golgari shaman
"The further into the future I look, the less certain my vision. Even now, the middle distance is obscured by fire."
Some view Domri's unlikely ascent as a sign of Ilharg the Raze-Boar's imminent return.
"Safe passage requires only a simple answer to a simple question, traveler."
The hook makes him feel brave, and the hat makes him feel fancy.

"The Golgari believe they should be given what they deserved. On this we agree."
—Tajic
The enormous can still be at the mercy of the small.
Raptors are clever enough to tear away a hard metal shell to get at the tasty morsel inside.
"Death is no excuse for disobedience." —Liliana Vess
"Nothing is more sacred than the gift of blood. Blessed are the vein that empties and the heart that is renewed."
Only the patrol's armor was found, so tainted with the acrid smell of sudden death that it could never be worn again.
"Don't make splashes. Make progress." —Tishana
"We are kin to the trees, and their strength is our own."
No ripples, no splashes, no warning.
Carefully following the thaumatic compass Bolas had given her, Vraska blundered straight into the River Heralds' trap.
"Time flows as the rivers do, toward an unknown sea. The wise know to look downstream."
Rocs' innate fearlessness makes them ideal mounts for emergency response.
Thievery requires subtlety, from the beginning of the heist to the end.
Cliffs echo and branches quake at the roar of life.
The roots run deep under stone and street, with strength that needs but a whisper to awaken.
"I long for peaceful times, when I may tend to my garden instead of our borders."
Some Gruul druids believe that boars are spawn of the great Ilharg, the mighty Raze-Boar who will one day rise and level the city.
Joining a guild, even the Gruul, would mean giving up some of his independence. He'd rather smash what he wants to smash.
The sly, stealthy warriors of the Slizt Clan survive by hiding in high ground and ambushing their enemies. Other Gruul call them skulkers and cowards, but only from a safe distance.
Gruul oracles see omens in all forms of destruction: the entrails of maaka's prey, the flight of vultures over a battlefield, the scattering of toppled stone.

"Tear down the city, lie by lie. Then throw it back at the liars, stone by stone."
—Domri Rade
The Rubblebelt grows restless.
Goblins' eager curiosity leads them to scavenging, petty theft, and the rigging of sleek pirate ships. Some stop at scavenging.
"That's the first time I've seen the ground do the running." —Captain Brinely Rage
Keld faced an apocalypse to fulfill a dire prophecy. Now Keldons have nothing left to believe in except themselves.
The Sun Empire's most sacred sites are protected by more than prayers.
Native to wide prairies and scrublands, falcons occasionally roost in dragon skeletons.
"This scum is barely worth the trouble."

"You will not be trained here. You will be forged."
—Commander Yaszen
"I will catch you, child of the sun. I will drink your life and leave you a husk, discarded in the shadows."
Though it was laid to waste by the brothers, many schools of magic trace their origins to the College of Lat-Nam, including the first Tolarian Academy.
The streets of Ravnica are full of former guild members now using their institutional skills for personal gain.

"My bowstring hums in tune with the song of the Worldsoul."
—Alcarus, Selesnya sagittar
The rising tide of Orazca's plunder lifted all ships.
"Industry without artistry is just a fancy way to fill the junkyard."
The greatest treasure of the deep is an echo from above.
The Sanctum Seekers were the first of the knightly orders to cross the sea and are still the most zealous.
"When history becomes too mournful, even good souls may choose to forget." — Shalai, voice of Plenty.
For the Legion of Dusk, the Immortal Sun is a source of eternal life. When they reclaim it, they will no longer be forced to subsist on the blood of the wicked.
"As the sun sets to make way for dawn, so we turn to darkness to bring about the coming salvation."
Thallids herd saprolings from place to place in search of detritus to feed them.
"I am most myself when I am least human."
"I hold the seed of our new beginning."
"The threads of magic that protect this place were woven by my will."

"Within each of us, the potential for great power waits to be released."
—Zija, Simic mutationist
A Gruul berserker is never unarmed.

"Whether we like it or not, our arrival has altered the landscape."
—Malcolm, navigator of the Belligerent
"The path of the stars is as reliable as the instruments that measure them."
"Have you seen your face? Trust me, this will be an improvement."
Feel it steel. Feed it gold. Feed it bone. In the belly of the furnace, the flames know no difference.
Shhh . . .
Where the light falls dim and blue on broken ships, secrets lie unclaimed.
An ancient nemesis rendered harmless long ago.
"When the waves pick up, either you find your feet or you lose your lunch."
