flavor_text: Stolen knowledge can never be stolen back.
Dusk follows the light.
"Shiv is a restless land. It heaves ash, bleeds lava, and scabs over in black obsidian." — The First Eruption

"How thoughtful of the Legion to train its soldiers to fit our spell's specifications."
—Nefara, Dimir agent

"Everyone who crosses that threshold is our most cherished friend. Everyone who crosses it again is our bitterest enemy."
—Trostani

"Think of the locket as a seed you bear, spreading life from Vitu-Ghazi across all of Ravnica."
—Heruj, Selesnya hierophant

"This Dovin Baan came from nowhere. Watch him. Read his letters. He is more than he appears."
—Lazav

"The Senate griffins overhead used to make people think of order and safety. Not anymore."
—Lavinia
Knights get the glory. Soldiers get things done.
The angel remembers her past lives like dreams. Her song held up meadows. Her blade drove back darkness. Her wings carried her across the ages.
Theologians now believe the Ancestor was another divine form of Serra.
She watches over the city just as Serra watches over all.
"You bound me with a contract only your death could end—and you thought me the fool?" —Liliana Vess
"I've seen Ravnica's fate. Believe me, I'm doing you a favor."
A threefold calamity with a single will.
"I am heir to many treasures. None is as precious as knowing how my ancestor lived her life."
The River Heralds would wreck a thousand ships to keep intruders from finding the golden city.
Shapers adapt nature to fit their needs and then return it to the way it was, leaving no trace of their passing.
Protection is woven into every vine and branch.
Today it's a miracle of architecture, a marvel of stained glass, a symbol of the Legion's power. Tomorrow, driftwood.
Those who wield the power of the sun protect the Empire from darkness.
When it passes, order defeats chaos.
Benalish glazeplate is stained with salts from the Rift Era and enchanted to deflect blows.

"There's something peculiar about the rain today."
—Janoc, Tin Street tinker
"The invaders cloak themselves in the shadows of dusk. Aerosaurs hide in the brilliance of the noonday sun." —Caparocti Sunborn
One pirate's wreck is another's reward.
The undisputed master of the mountains of Shiv.
Sometimes Shivan dragons toy with their food. Other times they just cook it.
The tools of invention became the weapons of revolution.
Over their long life spans, the larger trilobites accumulate vast treasure troves in their guts.
"Sometimes the only difference between a martyr and a hero is a sword." —Captain Sisay, Memoirs
No rampart can withstand the fury of a giant.
"Ready . . . uh . . . fire!"
To a siegehorn, there is no such thing as a dead end.
Suddenly, all the haggling didn't seem so important.
Dwell longest on the thoughts that shine brightest.
"These terms are acceptable to House Dimir. Shall we shake on it?"
Made to ward off the Grim Captain and silence the lure of undeath.
"Stay close! It's just a little farther."
A pair of domesticated griffins escaped from captivity a century ago. Now the skies are filled with the songs of their descendants.
"Control them? No. I gird them in armor and let them loose." —Yacha, Otepec huntmaster
"If you keep to the shallows, you'll never learn the secrets of the depths."

"Mystery is beauty. Within the unknown we plumb revelation."
—Vannifar

"Like our guild itself, this locket can stand for many things. You must discern what it means for you."
—Vannifar

"We have intel that some guilds have fallen under an invader's influence. Until we're sure, no venture succeeds."
—Lazav
"Prepare to be boarded."
Deception and misdirection are the heart of the pirate's arsenal.
He's the calm that hides the coming storm.

"This imprint was the familiar of a friend."
—Vivien Reid

"A better Ravnica begins with a better Simic."
—Vannifar

"When it comes to killing with precision, a soul is but a hindrance."
—Isareth the Awakener
Going to a Rakdos show is dangerous. Trying to leave early can be fatal.
Deep beneath the ruined continent of Otaria, there's a mine where goblins still work, ignorant of the destruction above.

"Life has no mistakes, only experiments."
—Yolov, Simic bioengineer
It flows like water over the forest floor, as deadly as the swiftest current.
Like a cross between a spider and a spyglass, but friendlier.
It skitters across the Shiv, each tendril hitting the ground with a sharp snap.
"They're so much more willing to parley once they're hanging from a boom by the ankle!"
Vampires call the gift of flight "exultation." For their enemies, it brings only sorrow.
Squadrons of skyknights are available for deployment around the clock, capable of reaching any district in the city within minutes.
"Sometimes an angel passes by and gives me a little nod, like, 'You're a daring one!' That always makes my day."
From the perpetual shadowsmoke that hung above the ship, a silent form emerged, lips curled with malice and anticipation.
"I was born to glory."
The municipal senate makes extensive use of the thopters, mostly to gather dirt on rival senators.
"Wherever the Threefold Sun shines, great wings may go." —Emperor Apatzec Intli III

"If you can't control your mount, I will control it for you."
—Mirela, Azorius hussar
"The amber sun smokes with fury, gazing on foes that gather like ants invading our home. We are ready! Blade and claw strike as one." —Huatli
"Cut the beasts out from under them and their strength is nothing." —Vona of Iedo, Butcher of Magan
The pirates had left the open sea behind, but they were still in their element: reckless adventure.

"I give them dreams so wondrous that they hesitate to return to the world of the conscious."
—Garild, merfolk mage
The magic of the River Heralds is so great that even a single shaman can fend off a pirate landing party.

"Relax. It's quite harmless. And it will dissolve completely in a month or two."
—Navona, Simic field tester
As Jhoira restored the Weatherlight, a mushroom growing in its hold unexpectedly became her first crew member.
"I'd rather be caught red-handed than leave empty-handed!"
The creation of new weapons demands the destruction of others.
"Come in, yes? Is warm!"

"Don't arrest him—enlist him!"
—Commander Yaszen

"I await your donation."
—Dasha, Orzhov priest
Foul-tempered, poorly trained, and mule-stubborn, the drake is the perfect test of the master's will.
Lurking beneath the murky waters of Ixalan's rivers, sailbacks can rip a meal off the shore in the blink of an eye.
They're fun to train—if you like stubborn, aggressive, and fiercely territorial.
He heard stars and saw thunder.
With Kumena in control of the Immortal Sun, the rapids rose from their riverbeds and the waterfalls took flight.
The first mistake the Grimnant knights made was bullying the owner of an Urborg corpse shop. Their second mistake was dying.

"You have given all to your kingdom, dear knight. Serenity shall be your prize."
—Queen Lian
Fools believe that Kolaghan's brood follows lightning storms. The wise know that it is the other way around.
The trainers were a gift of gratitude from the wizards of Tolaria West to the knights of New Benalia for their aid during the Talas Incursion.

"Don't waste time aiming, you lazy gob-slug! Fire!"
—Krenko, mob boss
"A fool's fire is quickly quenched." —Shaper Kumena
"I do not understand the future I see: the guilds subverted, the world at war, armies bent to a cruel conqueror's will."
Azorius sphinxes are loyal to the precepts of the law, not to any particular guildmaster—even one of their own kind.
"Be still." —Azor
"Do not think me blind to your true mission...or your true master, Grand Arbiter."
The conquistadors surrounded the dinosaur only to find that it had outflanked them.
"Every street's a stage, and every screaming bystander's an audience."
The Golgari adorn themselves with the exoskeletons of iridescent insects. It's only fair the insects do likewise.
Its mandibles can leave a rider in the clouds astride a headless griffin.
She breathes fair winds to tired griffins and lifts songbirds beyond the reach of stalking cats.
"The identifying ornamental growths of alpha thallids may be hereditary, or catalyzed by some chemical signal." —Sarpadian Empires, vol. III
As the irrepressible power of a dormant Multani courses through Yavimaya, the forest passes judgment on travelers and natives alike. Only the fungus prospers.
"What is this foul presence that defies the sun's cleansing rays?" —Itzama the Crested
"You gotta be pretty smart to live long as me, but not being able to die helps."
When the golden city opened, the dinosaurs inside were eager to greet the new visitors.
White as starlight on snow, it appears only on the eve of the winter solstice.
"The visions haunt me. I see the end of the world, brought on by the search for the Immortal Sun." —Shaper Pashona

card_faces: [{'object': 'card_face', 'name': 'Status', 'mana_cost': '{B/G}', 'type_line': 'Instant', 'oracle_text': 'Target creature gets +1/+1 and gains deathtouch until end of turn.', 'watermark': 'golgari', 'artist': 'Ben Wootten', 'illustration_id': '4d482200-5fb2-40cb-8693-dd48b256e21e'}, {'object': 'card_face', 'name': 'Statue', 'mana_cost': '{2}{B}{G}', 'type_line': 'Instant', 'oracle_text': 'Destroy target artifact, creature, or enchantment.', 'watermark': 'golgari', 'artist': 'Ben Wootten'}]

flavor_text: "Like the mighty armasaur, we will defend against all who invade our shores." —Itzama the Crested

"A massive new Izzet building project with an unstated purpose? Probably fine."
—Zija, Simic mutationist
One eye open to see the truth of the world. One eye covered to gaze at the goddess within.

"If the Fin Clade cannot produce a reliable venomous krasis, mobile in both air and water, then the Guardian Project will absorb its resources."
—Vannifar
No part goes to waste.

"What we begin, the End-Raze will finish. Then we will dance in Ravnica's rubble."
—Nikya of the Old Ways
The bedrock has many gifts to give.
"What you build, we will destroy . . . and bury you in the rubble!"
"Only one thing beats the freedom of the sea: the freedom of the sky."
"Go ahead, build another. I'll burn that down as well."
"Charge like a red-hot cannonball straight to your target. You slow down, you sink." —Captain Lannery Storm
"They're searching in the same direction we are. And for the same thing, I'll wager."
"A bolt to the eye, a blade to the neck. That's the way to clear the deck!"
In his hands, the wind can become a weapon or a means of escape.
"My shout is thunder and my fist is lightning!"

card_name: Storm the Vault // Vault of Catlacan

flavor_text: Imagine a thousand tiny mushrooms cropping up within your lungs.

"They said obey and you'll be happy. They said you'll be safe. But we're not safe. We're not happy. And we will not obey."
—Domri Rade
The pack that ambushes, eviscerates, and devours together stays together.
"Because the giant, implacable death lizard wasn't scary enough already." —Captain Brinely Rage

"Long after the land has given up the last of its secrets, there will still be mysteries in the depths of the sea."
—Kiora
"We have inherited the mysteries of the Thran, but few of the answers." —Jhoira
Any challenge to Azorius authority is met with swift and potent retribution.
When Huatli chooses a mount, its eyes glow with the flames of the sun.
"With Tilonalli's gifts, even the smallest of us can become great." —Huatli
"Pterodons tolerate no intrusion into their skies. Even the clouds must ask permission." —Mahuiz, Sun Empire archer
One alone is dangerous, and they are never alone.
"You take our wilds, we take your city."
"Before I let you wield one of these, let's see you dodge one!"
To the Sun Empire, any place where daylight brightens the jungle floor is sacred ground.
Just as the sun rises at dawn and the days lengthen in the summer, the Sun Empire has awakened after long years of quiet.
A king's knowledge does not vanish when the heart stops beating.
"I packed three more electroconduits into each test wand. You'll experience a brief tingling sensation."
When it passes, waves touch the sky.
All the books were dusty with disuse, save the one titled Camouflage and Its Practical Applications.
Though small, goblins can hold their own in a fight. Foolhardy confidence goes a long way.
"I'm about to make you famous. From the golden city to High and Dry, they'll talk about how fast you died!"
The pirates of the Brazen Coalition are the descendants of those displaced by the Legion of Dusk, and they are eager for vengeance.

"Now do you understand what we meant when we said *disperse*?"
—Eksari, Boros patrol leader
A swiftblade is an artist, each fiery trail of their blades a fleeting masterpiece traced on the air.
A warning shout would take too long.

"Oops!"
—Grupgrup, sluiceway technician
Say hello to your new friend.
"Take my blood if you want. Just don't take my gold!"

"The trouble with youths these days is that, in outright defiance of their elders, they refuse to be bought."
—Karlov of the Ghost Council
For the River Heralds, the Immortal Sun is an object of terror and devastation. The idea that anyone would retrieve it for their own use is utterly abhorrent.
"Yavimaya is aware, but not always awake. You will know the difference when you see it. — Karn
The mournful lowing of brushstriders warns of changing weather and ill winds.
The fire spell stuttered and broke. Its pieces reached Teferi out of rhythm, meaningless.

"Many wings haunt the skies these days. Few of them bear good tidings."
—Lavinia
In the quiet before a battle, Boros soldiers whisper prayers that steady their nerves and focus their minds.
"Your death will be a balm, your passing a welcome revision, and all will sigh with peace to know of your demise."
The dead who wander beyond the safety of the city crave only to spread their curse.
"Yavimaya is one being — one vastness of rippling leaves, one deepness of roots, and one chatter of animals — of which I am one part."

"You will kneel before me, even if I have to split the earth under your feet!"
—Ash Kronor, Keldon warlord
"Long ago, I enchanted an army of statues to guard Zhalfir. My homeland is gone, but its protectors remain." — Teferi
"I am the storm."
The first to arrive on Dominaria from their distant home, the marids are the oldest tribe of djinn and the most respected by storm and sea.
"Kinjalli sculpted humans from clay, but the dinosaurs were carved from unyielding stone." —Itzama the Crested

"Where the roots reach, there the temple rises."
—Niszka, Selesnya evangel
The Cabal soldier blinked and found day had become night, he had a face full of thistle seeds, and the old man was nowhere to be seen.
"The Tenth has always been my home. This city is constantly embroiled in one crisis or another, but I'm determined to protect my piece."
"I keep reminding myself we do this because others can't, because we love this city. If we don't save it, no one will."
A living remnant of the Ice Age.

"The presence of the strong will make you stronger."
—Yeva, Nature's Herald
From the eyes up, it's solid bone and stubbornness.
"The Ancestor saved us for a purpose."
"My ancestor Toshiro used to say, 'Life is a series of choices between bad and worse.' I'm a master of making great bad choices."
While Kaya is guildmaster, Teysa waits patiently at the center of the Orzhov web of power.

"More obedient than any dog."
—Tezzeret
Thelon of Havenwood created thallids as a food source in times of darkness. Thallids did the same with saprolings.
Some of the thallids that escaped into the fens of Urborg began emulating the Cabal's bloodsoaked rituals in their own peculiar way.

At the beginning of your end step, if you control seven or more lands, transform Thaumatic Compass.', 'colors': [], 'flavor_text': '"Clearly, it indicates the aetheric azimuth of . . ." —Jace Beleren', 'watermark': 'planeswalker', 'artist': 'Yeong-Hao Han', 'illustration_id': '7e7ecbcf-37a6-4960-83d4-0c7788af06b2', 'image_uris': {'small': 'https://img.scryfall.com/cards/small/en/xln/249a.jpg?1527431340', 'normal': 'https://img.scryfall.com/cards/normal/en/xln/249a.jpg?1527431340', 'large': 'https://img.scryfall.com/cards/large/en/xln/249a.jpg?1527431340', 'png': 'https://img.scryfall.com/cards/png/en/xln/249a.png?1527431340', 'art_crop': 'https://img.scryfall.com/cards/art_crop/en/xln/249a.jpg?1527431340', 'border_crop': 'https://img.scryfall.com/cards/border_crop/en/xln/249a.jpg?1527431340'}}, {'object': 'card_face', 'name': 'Spires of Orazca', 'mana_cost': '', 'type_line': 'Land', 'oracle_text': '(Transforms from Thaumatic Compass.)

flavor_text: It drains vitality from those it touches.

"Your life is a blinding light, your breath a gale, your pulse a deafening drum. Be still. Be still."
—Dahlya Trul, "Irbitov Lament"
The first law of Yavimaya is that guests may kill only to survive. As fires aren't needed in the warm weather, cutting trees for wood means death.

"Halana grew brambles to create a barricade around our camp, hoping that it would keep the wolves out. That was a mistake for which we almost paid dearly."
—Alena, trapper of Kessig

"I can think of no greater punishment than answering your question in full."
—Lazav
"It's truly the highest honor, isn't it? To be remembered? Pity for you."
Ral's storm crackled with mystical detections: Planeswalkers were infiltrating Ravnica.
The portal opens not to the past, but from it. Those who step through discover an unimaginable future.
It cares more about preserving the herd's territory than about preserving itself.
They glide through the undergrowth, drawn to sounds of disturbance. They attack in unison and all share in the kill. And then they move on.

card_faces: [{'object': 'card_face', 'name': 'Thrash', 'mana_cost': '{R/G}{R/G}', 'type_line': 'Instant', 'oracle_text': "Target creature you control deals damage equal to its power to target creature or planeswalker you don't control.", 'watermark': 'gruul', 'artist': 'Winona Nelson', 'illustration_id': '531a85eb-0b9d-4108-8fac-b75673fa94da'}, {'object': 'card_face', 'name': 'Threat', 'mana_cost': '{2}{R}{G}', 'type_line': 'Sorcery', 'oracle_text': 'Create a 4/4 red and green Beast creature token with trample.', 'watermark': 'gruul', 'artist': 'Winona Nelson'}]

flavor_text:
"Give 'em a push."
—Mogwin, goblin delinquent
The herds follow as new growth arises.
"It appears that nature has risen against us." —Captain Brinely Rage
"Nothing is too broken to mend."
The people of the Sun Empire worship the sun in three aspects. Tilonalli is the Burning Sun, associated with ferocity, fire, and passion.
"I am the ferocity of the Burning Sun. I am hide and feather, fang and claw."
Tazeem's embrace is harsh, but for those that call it home, nothing else will do.
"That giant didn't even see me, let alone catch me! And I was close enough to smell him! Of course, that's not saying much."
"There is always another way."
Whoever wins, the neighborhood loses.
The massive dominate through might. The tiny survive with guile. Beware the tiny who become massive.
The glorious city of Pachatupa is the center of the Sun Empire, and Tocatli, the emperor's palace, is its glowing heart.
The Tolarian Academies embrace a tradition of study and research while discouraging the kinds of experiments that ruined the original island of Tolaria.

"Reading it has given me a glimpse of what makes this deeply flawed city so very magnificent."
—Dovin Baan
"Light a torch and deliver this letter" were his instructions, which he unfortunately reversed.
"Unwelcome thoughts crowd my mind. Are they my own madness, or the whispers of another?" —Sarkhan Vol
Fblthp had always hated crowds.

"We've been practicing for this all our lives. This is the final test!"
—Korun Nar, Rubblebelt hunter
"In a healing world I write—I, who will never be healed. Let my last gift be one of memory: from a thousand lost thoughts, choose one, and remember my name."
Beyond the chaos of Ghirapur lies a vibrant world where aether flows through nature.
"I would advise you not to struggle." —Huatli
"The best kind of treasure is the kind that leads to more treasure!" —Captain Lannery Storm

flavor_text: His favorite food is kraul.
The sound of the trumpets lights a fire in the hearts of the bold and snuffs the courage of the cowardly.

"Margaret has traveled with me to the end of the world and back."
—Hewen Frit, merchant
A pet that can hunt both flesh and spirit is precious in a place where smiling assassins keep company with ghostly shadows.
He watches the pass in both directions, and all must pay his toll.

"Thread the torsos together with angel hair to ensure they will cooperate in battle."
—The Stitcher's Tome
The cold slowed their movements until only their panicked eyeballs swiveled beneath the ice.
In its territory, living is an affront.

"We grow strong by feasting on failure."
—Izoni
The undercity is always hungry.

"Now it's your turn to hide."
—Vraska
"You've strayed, overworlder."
The first thing the mist chills is the mind. Victims never cry out or even murmur in surprise.
Disputes within the Brazen Coalition can escalate from insult to broadside in the blink of an eye.
"Just imagine what's waiting around the bend. Adventure. Discovery. Riches for the taking. This is why I sail." —Captain Lannery Storm
A well-chosen word can restore a mind or snap its tethers.
"A problem is only a problem if you don't have the tools to correct it." —Jhoira
Ravnica's diversity produces blossoms of opinion in a rich soil of perspectives.
As the phantom flies overhead, the city of Vhelnish screams in silence.
"Wold you rather feel the edge of blade or the sharpness of my fangs?"
Centuries ago, one man's vengeance plunged the world into ice and darkness.
"Truly understanding even one volume can be a life's work." —Naru Meha, master wizard
The hammer strikes. The Flame awakens.
"Defeat is no reason for retreat. It is a sign we must redouble our efforts to win this fight."
"These pirates must answer for their ancestors, who renounced the Church of Dusk and sailed from Torrezon as heretics."
One day, they may be paragons of deadly elegance. For the moment, they possess nothing but thirst.
"A thick fog obscures the port of Leor, but it's not thick enough to muffle the screams." —Admiral Beckett Brass

"Your service shall be rewarded."
—Queen Lian
The Feast of Blood sends new life essence flowing through the vampire who partakes, manifesting as even greater strength and speed.

flavor_text: The clerics known as condemners punish those who do not recognize the righteous authority of the church.
"There's no need to sound the alarm. You are minding your post admirably. I am authorized. All is well."

"I sang songs of sorrow for my lost love. Imagine my horror when, one night, they were answered."
—Milana, Orzhov prelate
The bower shuddered. The stillness broke. The scurf shifted, and a being emerged from the flowers and ferns.
The dryads of the forest have no stake in Ixalan's conflict, but they hate to see any living being suffer.
"Ixalli's fertile rays enliven us all. Each of us is a testament to the sun's strength and love." —Chitlati, Lightning Rider

"Here, there is only truth."
—Barvisa, Azorius emissary
"Selesnya's soil is sacred, and you're about to meet it with your face."
"I trained with the Ghitu, and I respect the fire as they do."
"He is ambitious. Tireless. And utterly ruthless. Ideal for the frontier." —Viceroy Elia Sotonores, report to the queen

"The alliances were already frayed. All we do is find the loose threads and pluck."
—Lazav
Villagers employ watchdogs as guardians and companions. Druids prefer something a little bigger.
In theory, the Guildpact keeps guild feuds form spiraling out of control. Personal feuds, however, are not covered.
When it passes, the dead are displaced by flourishing life.
She has never touched a loom, yet the tapestries she weaves are vast and beautiful.
Golgari crops bloom in strange soil, touched only by long-traveled light.
Each of Vivien's arrows is an invocation of a species.
Orzhov vampires look for allies in unlikely places in case their new guildmaster turns on them. The fate of the Obzedat is proof of Kaya's power and her hatred of the living dead.
The Vodalian Empire tends to be insular. The scholarly Volshe caste are the exception, using education as an antidote to xenophobia.
Sometimes an eruption in Shiv produces something more dangerous than a mere river of molten rock.
"Fill the sky with stuff!"
A missing piece in search of a puzzle.
"For four hundred years, I have led armies of conquest. These lands hold nothing that can stand against me."
The purest devotion isn't the Blood Fast itself, but the craving that follows.
Abandoning both queen and church, he chose to follow power.
It wasn't long before the taverns of High and Dry were full of whispers about the new captain who could turn a person to stone with a glance.
"Kinjalli's encompassing rays herald new life in the moment of the sun's dawning." —Chitlati, Lightning Rider
"Our foes are many and mighty, but not as many as the trees or as mighty as the sea."

"Feeding a normal army is a problem of logistics. With zombies, it is an asset. Feeding is why they fight. Feeding is why they are feared."
—Jadar, ghoulcaller of Nephalia
When Captain Thorn adds a new ship to his fleet, he gives the crew a simple choice: follow me, or fall in the sea.
Those who intrude upon the Dimir seldom remember that they have done so.
Fog haunts the streets, rendering familiar as otherworldly, changing neighbors into shadows, and muffling cries for help.
Like all jungle plants, the vines must fight and claw for sunlight. Once their place is secured, they grow strong, sharp, and impenetrable.
Made by the mad for the work of the wicked.
"Trust me. The reward's not worth it."
War begins with one red ember.
"The old ways were for a winter world. We do what's best for us, not for the past. We are Keldons!" — Grand Warlord Radha

flavor_text:
"Be like the grazers of the Saruli. Keep your herd close, and stay alert for encroaching danger."
—Lalia, Selesnya dryad
Loitering is not only illegal but unwise, since those who stay too long in one place are apt to be stepped on.
The river is a powerful friend.
Few believe Duskmantle exists. Fewer find it. None live to bear witness.

"Something's causing electrospheric disruption in the blazekite's spire-vanes. Find the cause, and tell them to keep it up!"
—Juzba, Izzet tinker
In lives that have stretched for centuries, there are bound to be a few awkward silences.
He has a job to finish, and it's you.
"Look how they beg for the knife! The Demonlord has trained them well."
"Sure, I hear things. I hear plenty. But how am I to talk with this parched throat?"
Once part of a wealthy merchant's private zoo, the herd roams feral throughout the Tenth, where it will remain until the guilds can agree to relocate, cull, or befriend it.

"Walls crack. Buildings fall. Always the wilds return."
—Domri Rade
"Hear me, stone, root, branch: be the fist of this land. Turn back those who trample upon your domain." —Song of the Shaper
Goblins climb and swing with ease, whether through a pirate ship's rigging or a tree's branches.
Acolytes of the lost Lord Windgrace fight to keep Urborg relics out of Cabal hands.
"Your mind is too filled with foolish concerns to hear the subtle whispers that the breeze brings."
Drakes become especially voracious as they prepare for their autumn migration, hunting the city's thoroughfares from dawn to dusk.
"Currents are currents, whether in sea or sky."

"What wishes do they grant? Mostly pinching-related ones."
—Omik, superintendent of waterworks
"The study of magic began when the first mage taught herself to throw lightning." —Naban, dean of iteration
"The second mage learned to dissipate blasts of lightning. Threat and response: thus did the study of magic progress." —Naban, dean of iteration
"By all means, take another step toward the captain."
"They never found the body of young Josu, or that of his murderous sister." —"The Fall of the House of Vess"
Waterways carve their routes through the land to reflect the paths the aether streams cut through the clouds.
"The Great River will not be tamed."

"The best construction makes the most satisfying destruction."
—Domri Rade
When Belzenlok's lieutenant Yar-Kul grew too ambitious, the Demonlord transformed him into a maggot. The frog that ate the maggot grew and grew, until a ravenous spirit burst from its body.
"When their community grows cluttered, thallids begin a traditional bobbing dance, then trek out in all directions." — Sarpadian Empires, vol. III
Centuries ago, a mad god offered a simple trade.
"I do as I please, little mortal. Do go on about your wishes, though—they amuse me to no end."
The sky takes flight and the earth trembles.
"The wind whispers, 'come home,' but I cannot." — Teferi
Among the Zhur-Taa Clan, goblins are the first to enter battlefury. When the battle is over, the survivors are still frothing at the mouth, looking for someone to hit.
